description:
&lt;p&gt;Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is looking to recruit an experienced Physiotherapist to provide maternity leave cover for the role of Clinical Lead Physiotherapist for an experienced Physiotherapy Team working within Cardiology and Cardiac Rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This fixed term post would offer the successful candidate the opportunity to experience working in a leadership role through the provision of both clinical and non-clinical duties and involves the organisation and delivery of inpatient cardiology physiotherapy services as well as outpatient cardiac rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be dynamic, enthusiastic and have excellent communication skills. Experience of working with acute cardiac patients including heart failure is essential and it is preferable that applicants have direct experience of working within cardiac rehabilitation (or similar services) or can demonstrate detailed knowledge of these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLeanne McCarthyJob titleCardiac Rehabilitation Manager / Clinical Lead PhysiotherapistEmail addressLeanne.Mcarthy2@nhs.netTelephone number01253 955326&lt;/p&gt;
